Notes:
- The certification path is abstracted as a single CA-signed certificate certA = sign(pkA, skCA). B verifies certA using pkCA before using pkA.
- The signature on the token follows the description X{Info} = (Info, Xs[h(Info)]) by signing the hash digest of payload and sending both payload and signature.

